 bimodal distribution of\ncore-helium burning Red Clump (RC) giants in the UV colour magnitude diagram of\nNGC 416. A comparison of the stacked MUSE spectra of the two RCs shows the same\nmean Na abundance difference between the two populations. The results reported\nin this work are a crucial hint that star clusters of a large age range share\nthe same origin: they are the same types of objects, but only separated in age.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Sep 2020 17:00:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-30"}
