viours of soft tissues, instead of linear\nelastic, linear viscoelastic, and thermal-only modelling in the existing\nmethods. It also provides high computational speeds for computer-assisted\ntreatment systems towards enabling the operator to simulate thermal ablation\naccurately and visualise tissue temperatures and ablation zones immediately.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Sep 2020 09:04:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 31 Dec 2021 09:29:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-03"}
